<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-30-0048 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper describes the reasons, methods and equipment required for theinstallation of an Energy Management Control System. The principal objectivesfor installing such a system are to monitor all selected energy loadsfor cost allocation purposes, and to obtain considerable energy savingsthrough load forecasting, consumption control and the elimination ofexcessive peak loads. System components are off-the-shelf products, includingIBM compatible computers and OPTO input/output devices. QNX, the hostoperating system, provides the working environment for the computers.The operator interface is user friendly and completely menu driven, withmany on-line help screens.</TEXT></DOC>